body.description: Upgrade your home storage while adding modern style with the Teamson Home St. James Wooden Floor Cabinet with 3 Shelves. This decorative cabinet features a sleek white finish with a crown molded top and a minimalist silhouette for a beautiful addition to your space. The 3 included interior shelves make this cabinet a functional solution to your storage needs. Constructed from durable engineered wood, this storage unit is built to provide you with long-lasting organization. Easy, step-by-step instructions and all of the hardware needed for installation are included for quick assembly. Purchase this stylish floor cabinet alone or with other items from the St. James collection for a cohesive, updated look. The Teamson Home St. James Wooden Floor Cabinet with 3 Shelves measures 24" x 12.5" x 32" to provide accessible storage without taking up too much space in your living area or bathroom.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 5, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Had to take time for a review. I've had this cabinet for about a week, and was afraid to begin the unpackaging. Although it was delivered very fast, the box was beat to h*** and back. I just knew I'd have to ship back with bunged up corners on everything. The way each piece is packaged is amazing. Styrafoam everywhere, between each piece, foam wrap, heavy cardboard reinforcements on each corner ..... I'm truly impressed. I haven't counted the hardware, but the packaging is flawless. TEAMSON HOME the name I will look for when buying for my home.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars TRYING to be great
reviews.reviewText: I bought this nice cabinet for laundry product storage. Unfortunately, it’s too short to accommodate more than one shelf because the products are tall. The packaging was outstanding on this item. All of the pieces were well-protected by foam and padded sheets, and labeled according to the assembly instructions.. The connecting parts were also labeled and in a compartmentalized package. There was even a little bag labeled “extra parts”. Amazing. The assembly instructions were superb and written by someone who actually speaks English! Step-by-step instructions with diagrams were awesome. The composite pieces are heavy and well-constructed. You DO need two people to assemble, as recommended. The parts are sturdy/bulky and hard to balance by yourself.Two things affect my rating of this otherwise lovely cabinet. First, the back is made of cheap cardboard. This really surprised me, considering the quality of the rest of the unit. The first time I would accidentally hit it with a detergent bottle, I’m sure it would punch out. I had to buy two wooden sheets to replace the two cardboard ($40). Second, the finish has already started rubbing off on the corners. I have no clue how extreme this will become but I will have to keep some white touch-up paint at the ready, Otherwise, this is a small, sturdy cabinet that is easily tucked into a corner and looks pretty.
